5.3 Code Blocks
The code-block template enhances code display with titles and captions.

title: app.py language: python caption: Example Python function for calculating factorial
def factorial(n): “““Calculate the factorial of n.”“” if n == 0 or n == 1: return 1 else: return n * factorial(n-1)

6 Example usage
result = factorial(5) print(f”The factorial of 5 is {result}“)



title: styles.css language: css caption: CSS for a responsive button
.button { display: inline-block; padding: 10px 20px; background-color: #4CAF50; color: white; border-radius: 4px; text-align: center; transition: background-color 0.3s; }
.button:hover { background-color: #45a049; }
